text: The France women's national under-18 and under-19 is a national basketball team of France and is governed by the Fédération Française de Basket-Ball. http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/FIBA/fibaStru/nfLeag/p/nationalfederationnumber/282/nfProf.html It represents France in international under-19 and under-18 (under age 19 and under age 18) women's basketball competitions. ==FIBA Under-19 World Championship for women== {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;" |- !Year !width="50"| !! width=25| !! width=25| !! width=25| |- | 1985||colspan=4|DNQ |- | 1989||colspan=4|DNQ |- | 1993||6th||7||3||4 |- | 1997||colspan=4|DNQ |- | 2001||5th||7||5||2 |- | 2005||colspan=4|DNQ |- | 2007||colspan=4|DNQ |- | 2009||7th||9||5||4 |- | 2011||6th||9||6||3 |-bgcolor=silver | 2013||||9||7|||2 |- | 2015||5th||7||5||2 |- | 2017||5th||7||5||2 |- | 2019||colspan=4|DNQ |- | 2021||colspan=4|Qualified |- | 2023||colspan=4|TBD |- |Total|| ||55||36||19 |} ==See also== * France women's national basketball team * France women's national under-17 basketball team * France men's national under-19 basketball team ==References== u Category:Women's national under-19 basketball teams
